Multiple players have shown potential for the 2021-22 NBA Most Valuable Player (MVP) Award after one month of the regular season. They include Stephen Curry of the league's No. 1 team Golden State Warriors, Kevin Durant of the Eastern Conference leader Brooklyn Nets, Giannis Antetokounmpo of the reigning champions Milwaukee Bucks, Dallas Mavericks franchise player Luka Doncic and the defending MVP Nikola Jokic of the Denver Nuggets. Who is your choice from the five, or do you have anyone else on your mind? Host: Li Xiang Guest: Matthew Watson Cover designer: Feng Yuan Chief editor: Chen Ran Supervisor: Zhang Shilei